-- BRICS stand against Western sanctions - Russian foreign minister
-- By Alexei Anishchuk
-- Tue Jul 15, 2014 01:39PM EDT
-- None



FORTALEZA, Brazil, July 15 (Reuters) - Russian Foreign Minister Sergei Lavrov said on Tuesday that the BRICS bloc stood against one-sided economic and political measures by third countries, but that the emerging nations were not seeking confrontation with the West.

Speaking to reporters after a meeting between the leaders of Brazil, Russia, India, China and South Africa, Lavrov said the BRICS were opting for a common approach to resolve global issues. "The summit has confirmed that by speaking against one-sided steps in global politics and economy, BRICS members are not seeking confrontation, but are offering to work out collective approaches to resolve all (global) issues," he told reporters at a BRICS summit.